SIMPLE: waggle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waggle
<hw>Wag"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Freq. of
<ets>wag</ets>; cf. D. <ets>waggelen</ets>, G.
<ets>wackeln</ets>.]</ety> <def>To reel, sway, or move from side to
side; to move with a wagging motion; to waddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why do you go nodding and <qex>waggling</qex> so?</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Waggle
<hw>Wag"gle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Waggled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Waggling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To move frequently
one way and the other; to wag; <as>as, a bird <ex>waggles</ex> his
tail</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Waggle
<hw>Wag"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A waggling or
wagging;</def> <specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Golf)</fld>, <def>the
preliminary swinging of the club head back and forth over the ball in
the line of the proposed stroke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wag-halter</ent>⟦br⟧
